# MongoPilot Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in values as needed.
# cp .env.example .env
#
# NOTE: MongoPilot is a Tauri desktop application. It does NOT use runtime
# environment variables for secrets — API keys and connection passwords are
# entered by the user inside the app and stored in the app's local SQLite
# database. This file documents build-time and development overrides only.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Development server (Vite)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# Port used by `pnpm dev` (Vite default is 5173; tauri.conf.json points to 1420)
# VITE_PORT=1420

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tauri build overrides (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

# Override the app identifier (must be unique per OS bundle)
# TAURI_APP_ID=com.your-org.mongopilot

# Host/IP that Tauri's dev server binds to (used by vite.config.ts on mobile dev)
# Usually left unset — Tauri CLI sets this automatically when needed.
# TAURI_DEV_HOST=192.168.1.10

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# In-app AI provider (configured through the UI, not env vars)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# The following are NOT read from the environment — they are provided
# by the user through the Settings > AI panel at runtime and persisted
# in the local app database. Shown here for documentation only.
#
#   AI Provider:  openai | claude | custom
#   API Key:      sk-... / sk-ant-...
#   Base URL:     https://api.openai.com/v1  (or your proxy)
#   Model:        gpt-4o / claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022 / etc.
